      "message": "[warning] Line 361: Moving `callNotifications[nid] \u003d notification` inside `start` means a failed `startForegroundService` attempt leaves an unreachable pending notification in `callNotifications`. On Android S+, `ForegroundServiceStartNotAllowedException` is caught and `pingPush` may retry later, but the failed `nid` remains stored forever because `CallNotificationService` was never started to consume it. This can accumulate stale notifications during repeated blocked starts. Roll back the map insertion when starting the service throws, or insert only after a successful start path can consume it. For example:\n```suggestion\n                    callNotifications[nid] \u003d notification\n                    try {\n                        ContextCompat.startForegroundService(mContext,\n                            Intent(CallNotificationService.ACTION_START, null, mContext, CallNotificationService::class.java)\n                                .putExtra(NotificationService.KEY_NOTIFICATION_ID, nid)\n                                .putExtra(NotificationService.KEY_SCREENSHARE, startScreenshare)\n                                .putExtra(NotificationService.KEY_CALL_ID, id)\n                        )\n                    } catch (e: Exception) {\n                        callNotifications.remove(nid)\n                        throw e\n                    }\n```",
